messages.message:
A couple of interesting insights:
While asking the question in Hindi about my date of birth, it responded "Deepanshu ki date of birth text mein mention nahi hai." translating to "Deepanshu's date of birth is not mentioned in the text".

Asking the question in English though resulted in an output. The prompt determines the availability of a data point for the model.

The date of birth however, is reported as 16/01/2002 whereas the documents says 15/03/2002 which is my correct DOB. Maybe this is due to the deliberate low resolution that I gave as in input. But the resolution is good enough for the human eye to report 15/03/2002 as the DOB.
We will have multilingual support (Hinglish in your case) soon :slightly_smiling_face: cc: @Hari
Yeah OCR might have picked it as 16/01/2002 looking at the resolution
@vineeth are we using MSFT v3 max?
@Matt Weaver yes we are using v3 max now.
